title: For Sale:  Luger P08 S/42
postcontent:
This is a beautiful Luger P08 Vopo E G date S/42. Full serial number on the underside of the barrel is 8181 which is proper for G dated Luger. The receiver has two Mauser Military Proof DE/53 and DE/63. The barrel has a DE/63 stamp on the left side and a proof on the right. The DE/63 stamps are proper and within the known range for the gun’s serial number. The magazines matches the gun with “106” and “1” and "2", indicating a spare mag. The magazine has a great fit and the gun works just as it should, with a good release and the hold-open functioning properly.Vopo bakelite grips in very good condition, no cracks.
Full numbered parts include: Frame, receiver, underside of barrel. Small parts numbered “06” include: Sideplate, takedown lever, trigger, firing pin, extractor, hold-open latch, safety bar, safety lever, breechblock, middle toggle & rear toggle. Extractor was marked “Geladen". 
The G Date Lugers were produced in 1935 as Hitler and the Nazis tried to hide & disguise production. The Treaty of Versailles was still in effect and it limited the size of the German military and put rigid constraints on the types of weapons it could produce. The Third Reich was not supposed to produce Lugers with a 4” barrel in 9 mm, which is exactly what this is. The G was a secret code for the year 1935. The S/42 is a production code for Mauser. Reduced to $1100
